net.slashie.libjcsi
Class CSIColor

java.lang.Object
  net.slashie.libjcsi.CSIColor
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Comparable
public class CSIColor
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable

Allows for the use of custom colors. These colors are comparable for equality but the ordering of them has more to do with saturation than color, so if placed in order the output may not be what is expected. Has both a small pallet called DEFAULT_PALLET which contains the basic 16 colors from curses implementations. Has an extended pallet called FULL_PALLET which contains a wide variety of custom named colors. Can be used to make any color with aRGB values from 0-255.

Author:
Santiago Zapata, Eben Howard

CSIColor

public CSIColor(int pr,
                int pg,
                int pb,
                int pa)
A constructor with information for all color channels in the aRGB colorspace. All values should be between 0 and 255, with 0 be none and 255 being max of that color.

Parameters:
pr - Red value
pg - Green value
pb - Blue value
pa - Alpha (or transparency) value, with 255 being fully opaque and 0 being fully transparent

CSIColor

                int pg,

Parameters:
pr - Red Value
pg - Green Value
pb - Blue Value

getColorFromCode

public CSIColor getColorFromCode(int code)
Attempts to return a CSIColor object from the default pallet. If the int passed in is to large or small for a position in the default pallet then CSIColor.BLACK is returned instead.

Parameters:
code - the pallet position whose color is to be returned
Returns:
the color in the position at code or BLACK if code is outside the default pallet

getCodeFromColor

Parameters:

Returns:
either the default pallet index matching the color or -1 if no match
